Package: ggbrat
Type: Package
Title: Build 2D Brain Atlases from Surface Meshes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jonathan", "Rittmo", email = "jorittmo@proton.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for deriving 2D atlas geometries from different types of brain surfaces,
    meshes and annotations. The package combines Python-based visibility
    extraction with R-based sf workflows so atlas files can be prepared for
    ggplot-style plotting.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9; optional, for surface atlas construction)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
      R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    alphahull,
    dplyr,
    FNN,
    isoband,
    reticulate (>= 1.41.0),
    RNifti,
    sf,
    smoothr,
    stats,
    xml2
Suggests:
    concaveman,
    htmltools,
    shiny,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
 
